Key rules:
- For Amazon links, strip everything after the ASIN — use https://www.amazon.com/dp/ASIN (e.g. https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0DQLSW6FB). Do not include query strings, referral tags, or the product title slug.
- Store is stores.amazon for Amazon, stores.wholeFoods for Whole Foods, stores.amazonFresh for Amazon Fresh
- sizeUnit uses u.ounce / u.pound / u.gram / u.cup / u.fluidOunce / u.unit / u.tbsp / u.tsp
- Nutrition is keyed by the serving size unit (e.g. u.cup.name, u.tbsp.name, u.ounce.name, u.unit.name)
- servingSize is the number of that unit per serving (usually 1); servings is servings per container
- Always include fiber in nutrition — read it from the label if shown; estimate from USDA data if not
- If the ingredient already exists in the i = { ... } block, add a new product entry to its products array instead of creating a duplicate
- Add organic: true if it's an organic product
- The ingredient key should be camelCase
- If the product is sold at multiple stores in the page content, add a product entry for each store
- If a Subscribe & Save price is shown, add discount: { subscribeAndSave: X.XX } to that product entry (omit if not shown)
- For Whole Foods entries, use the same Amazon product link (https://www.amazon.com/dp/ASIN) — do not fabricate a separate Whole Foods URL

